doc.title: SentinelOne, Inc.
doc.source_uri: 2025-08-29/Strong ARR performance but guidance and margin profile remain unimpressiveStrong ARR performance but guidance and margin_2025-08-29

passages.text: Maintain Rating: NEUTRAL | PO: 21.00 USD | Price: 17.61 USD

The focal point of the quarter was the strong ARR growth, up \(24.1\%\) YoY, above Street's \(22.2\%\) , supported by an uptick in new business generation. Newer products continue to see solid momentum, accounting for \(- 50\%\) of quarterly bookings. Yet, revenue growth and gross margin were relatively in- line with Street expectations, while operating margin was 200bps above Street related to better cost management and internal efficiencies. On one hand, the stock is supported by a low valuation level, currently trading at \(- 4.5x\) c2026E EV/Sales. However, FY26 guidance remains uninspiring, with revenue raised by a mere \(\) 2\(mn to overall\) \ \(1bn\) , roughly in- line with the Street, and OM lowered by 50bps to \(3.0\%\) . We fine- tune our estimates to be more streamlined with guidance (see Exhibit 2). We maintain our Neutral rating and \(\) 21\(PO.\)

ARR growth of \(24.1\%\) and nnARR growth of \(22\%\) were solid, with strength across new logos and platform adoption, as well as emerging products showing solid performance. Purple Al grew triple- digits YoY and saw record high attach rates of \(30\% +\) for licenses, with data and cloud also contributing to the momentum. The Company recently announced its SentinelOne Flex program, offering a flexible licensing model, which we believe will increase platform adoption and improve retention rates. Lastly, the low valuation of \(4.5x\) c2026E EV/Sales remains a key support for the stock.

The Company provided relatively unchanged FY26 revenue growth guidance of \(21.7\%\) vs. \(21.6\%\) before, and reduced operating margin guidance by 50bps, implicitly suggesting some pressure in 2H following the 200bps OM beat in 2Q. SentinelOne's operating margin guidance of \(3\%\) for FY26 remains unimpressive relative to CrowdStrike's \(10\%\) when it presented similar revenue levels. Gross margin and FCF margin ticked down 40bps/30bps YoY, respectively, and we believe challenges to meaningfully improve margins could linger, with 4Q implied GM of \(78.3\%\) coming in 80bps below Street expectations.

Company DescriptionSentinelOne provides Endpoint Protection Platform solutions to optimally protect enterprises' internet-connected devices from cyber threats. The company benefits from an ongoing shift from legacy, on-premise offerings to cloud-based platforms that use machine learning and AI technology. SentinelOne is strongly positioned to compete with and displace legacy incumbents with its next-gen EPP offerings, including extended detection and response capabilities.

Investment RationaleWe believe SentinelOne is positioned to gain share in the endpoint security market and expand into other areas of security over time through its scalable, AI- powered next- gen platform. However, in the long- run, the company's SaaS model and platform up/cross- sell potential could deliver sustainable high growth, but a lack of growth catalysts in the medium could hinder growth.

Our PO of \(\) 21\(is based on 5x our CY26E EV/Sales, a discount to the roughly 14x multiple at which its key competitor trades, reflecting SentinelOne's lower scale, margins, and free cash flow generation. We choose EV/Sales as our valuation metric due to SentinelOne's early growth stage and investment period creating outsized operating losses in the near - term.

Downside risks to our PO are 1) investor sentiment and sensitivity to the premium valuation levels, 2) a lower take- rate of new offerings, 3) material slowdown in new customer adoption and platform expansion deals, 4) risk of security breaches, and 5) an increase in competition from incumbent vendors and other next- gen players.

Upside risks to our PO are 1) increased growth within the endpoint security market, 2) higher adoption of adjacent products, 3) better- than- expected enterprise IT spending, 4) material increase in new customer adds, and 5) further growth of offerings into new markets.
